    "1, with other models showing similar trends (App. C.4).",
    "We find that label bias, similarly to model performance, is highly sensitive to the choice of demonstrations, as indicated by the high variance across sets.",
    "Interestingly, the set of demonstrations that attains the worst performance also leads to strong bias, and vice-versa.",
    "In fact, we find that performance and bias are anti-correlated, with strong Pearson correlation for RSD (r \" ´0.74) and moderate for BiasScore (r \" ´0.30), indicating that when LLMs underperform in classification, it is often due to prompts that exacerbate bias.",
    "We leave further research into demonstrations that lead to biased and unbiased predictions to future work."
